law.catch_line: Ten-day grace period for filing of statements of financial interests.
law.text: A filer submitting a statement of financial interests within ten (10) days of the statutory deadline or the deadline authorized by the commission shall be subject to no penalty.
law.history: Created 1993 (1st Extra. Sess.) Ky. Acts ch. 4, sec. 24, effective September 16, 1993.
